LuCI gettext for luci-app-glinet-privacy (standard .lmo workflow, same idea as upstream luci-app-* packages)
============================================================================================================

Layout
------
  templates/glinet_privacy.pot     — template catalog (regenerate from sources; tooling fixes only)
  <lang>/glinet_privacy.po       — per-language PO (edit msgstr)
  (build) glinet_privacy.<lang>.lmo — installed to /usr/lib/lua/luci/i18n/ via OpenWrt Makefile po2lmo

Runtime: luci.glinet_privacy.i18n calls luci.i18n.loadc("glinet_privacy") so <%: … %> and translate() use the domain.

Regenerate POT / refresh PO stubs (repository root)
---------------------------------------------------
  python tools/extract-luci-i18n-strings.py
  python tools/i18n-build-po-from-pot.py

English po/en/ usually keeps msgstr = msgid; translate po/de/, po/uk/, etc.

OpenWrt package build (.lmo)
----------------------------
package/luci-app-glinet-privacy/Makefile sets PKG_BUILD_DEPENDS:=luci-base/host, runs po2lmo in Build/Compile
for every po/*/glinet_privacy.po, and installs glinet_privacy.*.lmo into the ipk.

  make package/luci-app-glinet-privacy/compile V=s

Router install without opkg (install.sh)
----------------------------------------
If po2lmo exists on the device, install.sh compiles PO → LMO when installing LuCI; otherwise English from sources.

Weblate (upstream translations)
-----------------------------
Gettext PO is compatible with Weblate “gettext PO” components.

Suggested (adjust paths if the component root is only luci-app-glinet-privacy):

  File mask for translations:  package/luci-app-glinet-privacy/po/*/glinet_privacy.po
  Monolingual gettext:         off
  New language template:       package/luci-app-glinet-privacy/po/templates/glinet_privacy.pot

Use LuCI-style language directory names (en, de, uk, …) so output stays glinet_privacy.<lang>.lmo.

After PO updates from Weblate: merge new msgids with msgmerge when templates change; re-run extract script when Lua/.htm change.

New language
------------
1. Add po/<lang>/glinet_privacy.po (copy po/en/ header; set Language / Language-Team).
2. No Makefile edit — Build/Compile discovers any po/*/glinet_privacy.po.
